premise_source_doc_sentence: Both marques have long and complex histories prior to their merger , going back to the 1940s , first coming together in 1968 as part of the ill-fated British Leyland conglomerate ; and later existed independently of each other as subsidiaries of BMW  (  in the case of Land Rover  )  , and Ford Motor Company  (  in the case of Jaguar  )  ; Ford later acquired Land Rover from BMW in 2000 following the break-up of the former Rover Group ; which was effectively the remainder of British Leyland .

Jaguar Land Rover Automotive PLC is the holding company of Jaguar Land Rover Limited , a British multinational automotive company with its headquarters in Whitley , Coventry , United Kingdom , and a subsidiary of Indian automaker Tata Motors .
The Land Rover Llama is a vehicle that was designed and developed by the British company Land Rover in the mid-1980s .
The principal activity of Jaguar Land Rover Limited is the design , development , manufacture and sale of vehicles bearing the Jaguar and Land Rover  (  including Range Rover  )  marques .
Land Rover is a car brand that specialises in four-wheel-drive vehicles , owned by British multinational car manufacturer Jaguar Land Rover , which has been owned by India 's Tata Motors since 2008 .
